title: Clinton joins Democrats against Pacific trade deal
text: > Top News Clinton joins Democrats against Pacific trade deal FILE - In this Nov. 10, 2011, file photo, then-Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton gives a speech at the East West Center on the campus of the University of Hawaii, Thursday, Nov. 10, 2011 in Honolulu as she attends the APEC Summit on Oahu. Clinton pushed hard dozens of times for the Pacific Rim trade deal she now opposes as a presidential candidate. Clinton said during the speech "There is new momentum in our trade agenda with the recent passage of the U.S.-Korea Free Trade Agreement and our ongoing work on a binding, high-quality Trans-Pacific Partnership, the so-called TPP. The TPP will bring together economies from across the Pacific, developed and developing alike, into a single 21st century trading community." (AP Photo/Marco Garcia, File)
